title.narrative: 1.1 HEALTH POLICIES & PLANS

description.narrative: National capacity to develop an integrated child health policy and its regional action plans based on child rights, the life cycle and inequities in social health determinants is enhanced., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, inequities in access to quality integrated child health interventions are reduced.

title.narrative: National capacity to develop an integrated child health policy and its regional action plans based on child rights, the life cycleand inequities in social health determinants is enhanced.

description.narrative: This programme component successfully made up for delays encountered because of the pandemic, despite the heavy involvement of the Ministry of Health (MoH) in preparing and rolling out the COVID19 vaccination campaign during 2021. Important health and nutrition strategic plans and programmatic guidelines were developed to promote child- and equity focused approaches and address the multiple determinants of health through inter-sectorial and community engagement. The next course of actions for 2022 is to move from central to lower levels, translate these action plans at regional level and test the newly developed tools at small scale before their generalization | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
